@Timinator Thank you for inviting me to review this puzzle. Actually I solved it soon after it was first published and I didn't see any issue with it, so I didn't leave any comment.

I think the difficulty is appropriate there. A player who solved a 9x9 Sudoku puzzle can adopt their code to solve the 16x16 puzzle relatively easily, and that also paves the way for solving this 25x25 challenge.

One thing just pops to my mind though. Have you checked whether each case indeed has no more than one solution? I haven't further improved my slow 25x25 Sudoku solver since last time, so it'll be too slow for my solver to check that :P (I'm sorry if you've checked, mentioned it before and I've missed it.)
